textBeforeTable: Roster Locals will recognize the presence of 6-foot-11 BYU product Trent Plaisted, a second-round pick of the Pistons in 2008 who spent last season overseas. First-rounder Austin Daye, who needs to add some bulk to a promising 6-foot-11 frame, will look to prove that leaving Gonzaga after just two seasons was no mistake, while veteran guard Will Bynum hopes to build on his strong finish to the 2008-09 regular season, during which his minutes and production steadily increased. The Pistons took Swedish big man Jonas Jerebko in the second round last month, making him the first Swede ever taken in the NBA Draft.
